      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ingratiator</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Higgins letter scores James Traub's July 30 portrayal of US Senate candidate Rick Lazio as mediocre0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I am tiring of attempts to paint candidates as mediocre simply because they may be moderates. As for the ''candidate from 'Pleasantville,''' we've already seen what we get when we elect clever people whose lifelong plan is to hold higher office for its own sake. New York could do a lot worse than electing a ''nice, average guy'' who's ''a little smarter than usual.''</p>
        <p>Paul Higgins  St. Louis</p>
      </block>
